    "recap_headline": "United States Air Force Academy",
    "recap_text": "WACO, Tex. \u2013\nThe Falcons (3-11) dropped a pair of games, 5-4 and 6-1, to Baylor (9-6) on Sunday afternoon at Magnolia Field at Baylor Ballpark. Air Force hitters tallied nine hits in both games while the pitching staff combined for 14 strikeouts across the doubleheader.\nAir Force 4, Baylor 5\nAir Force recorded nine hits in the opener, led by\nTripp Garrish\nwith two and an RBI.\nJ.D. Wolff\n,\nKayden Bradshaw\n, and\nCam Anstey\naccounted for the Falcons' remaining RBIs.\nJosh Holst\ntook the initial start Saturday evening, throwing 1.1 innings with two strikeouts before the game was suspended due to weather. When play resumed Sunday,\nJordan Watkins\n(0-2) took over and went three full innings, striking out two while allowing four runs.\nMarcus Downing\nclosed the final 3.2 innings with one strikeout and one run allowed.\nThe Falcons struck first for a 1-0 lead in the top of the second.\nWyatt Hanoian\nopened the inning with a single to left, advanced to second on a wild pitch, and moved to third on a groundout by\nLuke Elmore\n. Wolff followed with an RBI groundout up the middle to bring Hanoian home.\nThe game was suspended shortly after with one out in the bottom of the second inning.\nAfter play resumed Sunday, Baylor evened the score at 1-1 in the bottom of the third before taking a 2-1 lead in the fourth.\nA three-run homer in the fifth extended the Bears' advantage to 5-1.\nAir Force mounted a late rally in the top of the ninth, plating three runs to pull within one. Back-to-back singles from Elmore and\nBlake Campbell\nput runners aboard before\nBen Niednagel\nmoved them over with a groundout. A throwing error by Baylor's shortstop allowed\nKayden Bradshaw\nto reach while Elmore scored. Pinch hitter Anstey followed with an RBI double to right, bringing Campbell home, and Garrish drove in Bradshaw with an RBI groundout. The Falcons' comeback attempt fell just short, 5-4\n.\nAir Force 1, Baylor 6\nThe Falcons again tallied nine hits in the second game, with seniors Garrish,\nWalker Zapp\n, and Niednagel collecting two apiece. Zapp accounted for Air Force's lone RBI.\nBowen Brantingham\nmade the start (0-2), matching his season high with 4.1 innings pitched while striking out four and allowing three earned runs.\nDavis Rhyne\nrecorded one out and allowed three runs before\nSam Hentges\nentered and tossed 1.1 scoreless innings with a strikeout.\nEaston Miller\nclosed the game with two scoreless innings and two strikeouts.\nBaylor was first on the board in the bottom of the second inning, taking a 2-0 lead.\nThe Falcons responded in the top of the third to cut the deficit in half. Campbell and Garrish opened the inning with consecutive singles before Zapp delivered an RBI double to plate Campbell and make it 2-1.\nThe Bears broke the game open in the bottom of the fourth, scoring four runs to extend their lead to 6-1.\nAir Force had multiple scoring opportunities with runners on base throughout the game but were unable to capitalize.\nThe Falcons return home next weekend for their home opener and the start of conference play, hosting UNLV from Friday, Mar. 13 through Sunday, Mar. 15 at Erdle Field."
